      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 386: The accessible description always announces online/offline presence for every list item, including non-contact conversations where presence may be unavailable or not meaningful. That can produce misleading screen-reader output such as \"Everyone is offline\" for a swarm with no presence data. Gate the presence sentence on an explicit availability condition, or omit it when presence is unknown.\n```suggestion\n        if (Presence \u003d\u003d\u003d 2 || Presence \u003d\u003d\u003d 1) {\n            constructedDescription.push(JamiStrings.presenceStatus.arg(IsCoreDialog ? JamiStrings.oneToOnePresenceOnline : JamiStrings.swarmPresenceOnline))\n        } else if (Presence \u003d\u003d\u003d 0) {\n            constructedDescription.push(JamiStrings.presenceStatus.arg(IsCoreDialog ? JamiStrings.oneToOnePresenceOffline : JamiStrings.swarmPresenceOffline))\n        }\n```",
